> Hello Rafaella,
> Please see below [in blue] my responses to the questions in your email =
below dated September 6, 2025.
> Please also find attached a copy of the =E2=80=98Material Damage =
Report=E2=80=99 & the =E2=80=98Scope of Works=E2=80=99 which relates to =
the damage report.
> I have done my best to answer the specific questions that you have =
raised. My general response to your enquiries is summarised as follows:
> =20
> All material and documentation of any form, in respect of your claim, =
is discoverable and is available to be provided to you. This will remain =
your enduring right through-out the claim process.
> I will need to work closely with your Claim Manager to ensure the =
information that you are requesting is provided to you in a timely =
manner. I am wiling to assist the Claims Manager in this respect.
> All aspects of potential damage which you are seeking to receive =
assurances on can be responded to on an individual basis. I am unable to =
provide those responses to you in this email, as I will require =
consultation and input from the relevant specialists and consultants.
> =20
> I think the most constructive next step would be for me to schedule a =
meeting with the key stakeholders within Tower Insurance and following =
that provide you with the clarification that you have requested.
> Please allow me to schedule a meeting with my colleagues and take the =
time required to provide you with a considered and comprehensive =
response.
> Best Regards,
