> On 29 Jul 2025, at 3:40=E2=80=AFPM, Grant Metson =
<Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz <mailto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz>> wrote:
> =20
> Hello Rafaella,
> Allow me to respond with answers to your enquiries as below:
> =20
> Asset Restore will be responsible for removing the gib-linings and =
clearing the property of ant damaged items such as skirting boards, =
doors, panels, etc. This will allow us to attend the property when it is =
clear and clean and complete our structural assessment of the property.
> The structural assessment will be undertaken by Tower Assessors [Chris =
or Grant] in conjunction with ASURNZ - Towers Technical Building =
Consultants. This inspection will produce a technical report which will =
form the basis of the =E2=80=98scope of works=E2=80=99. This is the =
correct process to determine the repairs which are required to the =
property. The scope of works will be shared with you, and we can review =
it onsite on a line-by-line basis to ensure that you are satisfied that =
it covers all the claim related repairs that are necessary.=20
> =20
> A current status update on the structural assessment and any scoping =
completed to date; As explained above this will occur as soon as Asset =
Restore have completed the cleaning and stripping out of the property. =
No scoping for repairs has been completed to date. This is the next =
phase of the claim progression.
> =20
> A proposed timeline for the next phases: removal, scoping, approvals, =
tendering, and repair; Estimates on start dates for the following claim =
progression phases:
> Removal of gib linings and other elements to allow structural =
appraisal and scoping =E2=80=93 completed by Friday August 8.
>=20
> Structural Assessment and draft scope of works document =E2=80=93 =
Completed by Friday August 15.
>=20
> Final scope of works shared with customer for sign-off =E2=80=93 =
Completed by Friday August 22.
>=20
> Tendering process to follow scope -of-works approval =E2=80=93 2 weeks
>=20
> Repair works able to commence Mid-September
>=20
> Confirmation of the parties responsible for each stage and how updates =
will be communicated.
> Asset Restore =E2=80=93 Clean-up & strip-out. All communications =
documented in writing.
> ASURNZ =E2=80=93 Structural assessment and producing scope of works. =
Reports and scope provided in writing.
> Tower Insurance - Tendering process =E2=80=93 all documents shared =
with customer and provided in writing.      =20
> =20
> =20
> My mandate is strictly around structural assessing and the repairs =
required to your house.
> I will ask the Claims Manager for your contents claim to respond to =
your concerns with the laptop and phones.
> I will ask the Motor Claims Manager to respond to your concerns with =
the EV vehicle.
